Over priced, bad food, watered down drinks and ok service. They are a dive bar experience for a nicer bar price tag. I have had several of their food items and they are all bad. Every time I get a drink here it’s mostly water, even when I ask for just soda. Not worth it. I have been to plenty of dive bars to know when I am being ripped off and this place is one of them. The service is ok, but you can tell that they only take care of the people who order a lot of booze. I ordered water, and food, one time and I was the last to get my food and it was cold. Didn’t see the waitress again for 45 minutes. We were one of three tables and somehow it took 2hrs for our lunch even though our party was ready to order as soon as we sat down. They seem friendly enough, but they aren’t, I ordered a well gin and sprite and somehow got mostly water and sprite. A person next to me ordered a double in a tall with sprite and got mostly alcohol and paid just a bit more than me, but he ordered two right in a row. He definitely had alcohol in his, mine... not so much. I will probably go back again, but not to order anything, but because my co-workers like the place since it’s right there, but they are not worth the money. If I don’t at least get tipsy on an empty stomach after one hard alcohol drink I know a place is ripping me off. I don’t drink often and at home I easily get drunk on one 4% beer on an empty stomach so I know what’s up. Had a long island iced tea and a gin and sprite and was barely buzzed. I hadn’t eaten much of anything that day and should have felt drunk after my first drink, instead I left sober after two hard alcohol drinks and 1.5 hours. My last drink I finished a half hour before I left so I should have felt it by then. I give places a few tries before rating them because there is always an opportunity for a mess up or someone having a bad day, no, this place is consistently upsetting and *meh* at best. I wish I could say I liked them, but no, I won’t be wasting anymore of my money at this place.  Side note: I hate buying alcohol/drinks at bars because I could have spent less at the store and gotten more. I really don’t like wasting money at bars so when a place is a REAL rip off, I can’t stand it.
